<br>
In a &quot;raid&quot; situation where you do want to keep mobs coming, IE Kael, TOV (regular), TOV (HoT)....you can keep those mobs coming much faster and much more furious with a couple mages there keeping a stockpile of rods on the ground, and dealing damage when needed.  Once again in this instance..3-4 clerics and a couple of mod rod 2'ing mages &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; 4-5 clerics all by their lonesome.  Not to mention Druids who spend half their mana with every cast of PoTG, and various other buffers able to not hold up the raid to med because of our nifty little rods.<br>
<br>
Maybe our raids are crappier...maybe my guild leader is a dope...because they understand, and hold in HIGH value, the utility of a well played magician who is there to help the raid succeed instead of bitching that they don't put the hurt on mobs like they used to.<br>
<br>
I don't blame VI for ignoring mages....we raise an outcry about not being useful on raids because we can't use our pets..so they give us spells like COH, Mala line, upgraded Mod Rods, summoned items with pretty damn good resists, lowered resistances on high lvl mobs so our nukes will land, but even with all that...we still bitch and bitch.  /shrug  I agree with the above poster who said you need to learn your new role and embrace it, or just stop (per the subject)..cause it is useful.  Roles change...it happens...you need to learn to grow into them.<br>
<br>
note: Get me started on COH abilities in Luclin, and you'll see a Jekyl/Hyde turnaround.<br>
