<br>
Let's break it down ... there are raids like Hate, Fear, PoG, Kael and HoT where you want clear MOBs as fast as possible.  Mod Rods aren't always needed and can sometimes be a hassle.  There isn't too much use for them unless maybe on a CR if you don't happen to have Clerics there with a Mr. Limpy(tm) stick.<br>
<br>
Then there are raids where a single MOB takes 10 minutes to kill and requires a 5 to 6 Cleric CH chain.  Mod Rod 2 is a godsend and adds a HUGE amount of value to Mages being there.<br>
<br>
And Tomlyn said it right ... Mages get KEI from a Chanter ... Mages summon MR2s and hand them to EVERYONE on the raid.  Mage meds back to full (doesn't take long now with KEI and AoE Mana song) while raid is still buffing/preping/pulling.  Right before the MOB arrives everyone who doesn't need a rod drops it on the ground.  Mage nukes to his hearts content to help kill UberMOB_001 while Clerics/Wizzys/Whomever picks up the rods if they need them.<br>
