<br>
1) &quot;We do not rate with any of the other damage dealing classes in the game&quot;.<br>
<br>
In my experience, pre-Kunark, doing PoH/PoF raids, the caster groups were always the XP (&quot;KS&quot;) groups.<br>
<br>
These days, it's the group with the most melees in it.  The word you would use to rate mages with the other damage dealing classes would be &quot;lower&quot;.<br>
<br>
2) &quot;We do not rate with any of the other utility/support classes in the game.&quot;<br>
<br>
Necros can be mana batteries, but their ability to battery has the advantage of not taking away the target's health.  They're much better self-contained batteries, converting their health into mana, sucking up health and transferring mana to whoever needs it.  I still maintain that this is the most insulting ability in the game, but at least they have a good implementation of it.<br>
<br>
Shaman and enchanters are all the debuffing you need.<br>
<br>
The only <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> real</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> service that magicians provide is COH.  The rest of our summons are largely a service to people who forgot to bring something.  Like their own food.<br>
<br>
While this is ammusing, I wouldn't call it a great support ability.  I don't think of the coke machine down the hall as a great support/utility device towards software development.  It's nice to have, but I could always bring my own Cokes to work if it wasn't there.<br>
<br>
3) &quot;We are no longer in the top half of the soloing classes&quot;<br>
<br>
#1) Enchanter.  Trickier, but fastest leveling class if well played.<br>
#2) Wizard.  Most efficient quad-kiting.<br>
#3) Druid.  Second most efficient quad-kiting.<br>
#4) Necro.  Heals, mana regeneration, fear kiting.<br>
#5) Bard.  Insane kiting/charmfighting ability outdoors.<br>
#6) Shaman?  Shadowknight?  Mage?<br>
<br>
If we're in the top half, it's a close call.<br>
